  "prompt": "Does sound travel through empty space?",
  "response": "No, sound cannot travel through empty space. Sound is a mechanical wave, which means it requires a medium (such as air, water, or solid objects) to transmit the vibrations. In space, which is a vacuum devoid of matter, there aren\u2019t any molecules to carry these vibrations, so sound waves cannot propagate. This is why, for example, astronauts in space communicate via radios rather than hearing each other directly.",
